The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Thursday, December 18, 2003 				 S amp;P revises outlook on 7 Indian firms
 OUR CORRESPONDENT																								Mumbai, Dec. 17: Standard amp; Poors (S amp;P) today revised its outlook on foreign currency ratings on seven companies, including Reliance Industries (RIL) and Indian Oil Corporation (IOC), to stable from negative.																								The rating revision followed a similar action on Tuesday, when the global agency upgraded Indias foreign currency rating to stable. The other companies whose outlook were raised included Indian Railway Finance Corporation, National Hydroelectric Power Corporation (NHPC), National Thermal Power Corporation, Power Finance Corporation, and Tata Power Company.																								S amp;P said this action reflected the significant improvement in the external sector of the country and rising current account earnings and external liquidity as a result of the growing dynamism of the private sector. However, the outlook on the local currency ratings on India remains negative, it added.																								The outlook on NHPCs local currency BB+ rating, it pointed out, remains negative in line with the outlook on the sovereigns local currency rating. 
